<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/28(Thu.) How do your morals compare? / When do kids start to care about other people's opinions? (Host: Josh)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=338&amp;p=354#p354"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Session I - How do your morals compare?</span><br /><br /><a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50487054" class="postlink">https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50487054</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion</span><br />Q1: What did you get in the moral quiz? Does a higher score mean higher morality?<br />Q2: What are the best examples of actions that are moral, even uplifting, but illegal?<br />Q3: Can morality be rated or judged?<br />Q4: Is morality subjective or objective? Why?<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II - When do kids start to care about other people's opinions?</span><br /><br /><a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/sara_valencia_botto_when_do_kids_start_to_care_about_other_people_s_opinions" class="postlink">https://www.ted.com/talks/sara_valencia_botto_when_do_kids_start_to_care_about_other_people_s_opinions</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion</span><br />Q1: How do you teach kids about other people's opinions?<br />Q2: How have people learned to stop caring about other’s opinions?<br />Q3: Do you care about other people's opinions of you?<br />Q4: How do you tactfully deal with people's opinions about you?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:20 p.m. Free talk<br />7:20 p.m. --7:50 p.m. First topic discussion<br />7:50 p.m. --8:15 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:15p.m.-- 8:45 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />8:45 p.m.-- 9:00 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br /><br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=49">josh</a> — Sat Nov 23, 2019 12:18 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
